From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GitHub Copilot <copilot@local>
Date: Tue, 2 Jun 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] checkpoint: fallback to copy on link ioerror

Some filesystems used by the Unikraft port do not report unsupported
hard-link operations as NotSupported. Instead, LinkFile() can surface an
IOError, which prevents Checkpoint::CreateCheckpoint() from falling back
to copying live files.

Treat IOErrors from the optimistic hard-link path the same way as
NotSupported so the checkpoint code degrades to the existing copy path.
This keeps the checkpoint utility usable on filesystems that lack link(2)
support but still support regular file copy and rename.
---
 utilities/checkpoint/checkpoint_impl.cc | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/utilities/checkpoint/checkpoint_impl.cc b/utilities/checkpoint/checkpoint_impl.cc
index a7f0c2e..6db1482 100644
--- a/utilities/checkpoint/checkpoint_impl.cc
+++ b/utilities/checkpoint/checkpoint_impl.cc
@@ -278,7 +278,13 @@ Status CheckpointImpl::CreateCustomCheckpoint(
       if (same_fs && !info.trim_to_size) {
         s = link_file_cb(info.directory, info.relative_filename,
                          info.file_type);
-        if (s.IsNotSupported()) {
+        // Some runtimes report unsupported hard links as IOError instead of
+        // NotSupported. Fall back to copying so checkpoint creation still
+        // works when link(2) is unavailable.
+        if (s.IsNotSupported() || s.IsIOError()) {
+          if (s.IsIOError()) {
+            ROCKS_LOG_INFO(db_->GetDBOptions().info_log, "Falling back to copy for %s after LinkFile IOError: %s", info.relative_filename.c_str(), s.ToString().c_str());
+          }
           same_fs = false;
           s = Status::OK();
         }
